title: Poetry Out Loud Suburban Chicagoland Regional Final
description:
At the Suburban Chicagoland Regional Final for Poetry Out Loud, high school students will recite world-renowned classic and contemporary poetry, as they compete for a trip to the State Finals in Springfield. The small group of Regional Finalists represents thousands of students who have participated and competed in their schools.

Poetry Out Loud: National Recitation Contest is sponsored by the National Endowment for the Arts and The Poetry Foundation, and, in Chicagoland, by the Illinois Arts Council in partnership with Literature for All of Us.
